      <description>&lt;div style=&#34;position:relative; clear:both; padding:0;&#34;&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;img src=&#34;https://duragauge.github.io/img/chapter-2/art-artist-brush-102127.jpg&#34;  title=&#34;Photo by Daian Gan from Pexels&#34;  alt=&#34;Photo by Daian Gan from Pexels&#34; style=&#34;display:block; width:100%; height:auto;&#34; &gt;&#xD;&#xA;  &lt;span style=&#34;position:absolute; height:auto; bottom:0em; right:0em; margin:0;  padding: .1em .3em;  color:white;  font-size: .8em;  background:rgba(0, 0, 0, 1);  text-align:right;  z-index:5;  opacity:0.65;  border-radius:.3em 0em 0em 0em;&#34;&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;a href = &#34;https://www.pexels.com/photo/brush-painting-color-paint-102127/&#34;&gt;Photo by Daian Gan from Pexels&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;br&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;introduction&#34;&gt;Introduction&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Part of the enjoyment of art comes from its patterns of sound and color and motion.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Patterns are also an essential part of mathematics.  The British mathematician G. H. Hardy once said that &lt;em&gt;&amp;quot;A mathematician, like a painter or a poet, is a maker of patterns.   If his patterns are more permanent than theirs, it is because they are made with ideas&amp;quot;&lt;/em&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
